    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.6112/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 664.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith in copy and
                    translation Decree No. 83, which revives the Zapata concession upon terms which
                    seem to conform with the Department’s previous objections.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Summary.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head"
                        >[Untitled]</head>
                    <p>Decree No. 83 of January 31, 1913, repeals Decree No. 758 of August 14, 1012,
                        which suspended Decree No. 556 of June 18, 1912; this renewal of the
                        operation of No. 556 is made in view of the withdrawal of the objections
                        that had been made [by the United States] thereto, and in view of the
                        amended interpretation to be given that decree, agreed to by the
                        concessionaire, and here stipulated [embodying the amendments mentioned in
                        the instruction of January 11, 1913, to the American Minister].</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
